lead_paragraph: A triple-bogey seven dropped Bryson DeChambeau four shots from the lead at the Masters, but the closing-hole blunder failed to dampen the spirits of the American amateur on Friday.

headline.print_headline: Amateur Impresses Despite Final-Hole Stumble at Masters
